---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import MobileInstallNotice from "../../components/MobileInstallNotice.astro";

// Canonical manifest URL served from the Cloudflare Pages deploy.
// If/when `addin.blackletter.studio` is wired up, update this URL and
// nothing else on this page needs to change.
const manifestUrl = "https://fair-copy-addin.pages.dev/manifest.xml";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Install Fair Copy"
  description="Four-step walkthrough to install Fair Copy in Microsoft Word — sideload the manifest, open a document, click the ribbon button."
>
  <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-oxblood mb-6">
    Black Letter Studio / Fair Copy / Install
  </p>

  <h1 class="font-display text-2xl sm:text-4xl leading-none tracking-tight mb-8">
    Install <em class="text-oxblood not-italic font-normal">Fair Copy.</em>
  </h1>

  <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mb-12">
    Four steps. Under two minutes. Works in Word for Mac, Windows, Web, and iPad. The Microsoft AppSource listing is in review; this sideload path installs the same add-in from the same domain &mdash; it just skips the store search.
  </p>

  <MobileInstallNotice subject="Install Fair Copy when I'm at my desktop" shareUrl="https://blackletter.studio/fair-copy/install" />

  {/* ------- Download button (hidden on phones via Mobile notice above) ------- */}
  <section class="py-8 border-y border-black/10 my-8 hidden md:block">
    <div class="bg-paper border border-oxblood/30 rounded-md p-8 max-w-xl">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-oxblood mb-3">
        Step 0 &mdash; download
      </p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-xl mb-3">Get the manifest file</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-soft mb-6">
        A <em>manifest</em> is a small XML file that tells Word where to load Fair Copy from. Download it once; Word keeps a reference after that, and updates ship automatically from our server.
      </p>

      <a
        href={manifestUrl}
        download="fair-copy-manifest.xml"
        class="inline-block bg-ink text-paper px-6 py-3 rounded-md text-sm font-medium hover:bg-oxblood transition-colors"
      >
        Download manifest.xml &darr;
      </a>

      <p class="text-xs text-ink-soft mt-4 leading-relaxed">
        Direct link: <a href={manifestUrl} class="text-oxblood underline break-all">{manifestUrl}</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ------- Step 1 ------- */}
  <section class="py-10 border-t border-black/10">
    <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-oxblood mb-3">Step 1</p>
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl mb-4">Open Word and find &ldquo;Add-ins&rdquo;</h2>

    <p class="text-ink-soft max-w-2xl mb-6 leading-relaxed">
      Exact path varies by platform, but the words &ldquo;Add-ins&rdquo; or &ldquo;My Add-ins&rdquo; always appear. Here&rsquo;s where to look:
    </p>

    <ul class="space-y-3 max-w-2xl text-sm text-ink-soft">
      <li>
        <strong class="text-ink">Word for Mac and Windows (2019+):</strong> Home tab &rarr; <em>Add-ins</em> button (far right) &rarr; <em>More Add-ins</em> &rarr; <em>My Add-ins</em> tab.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-ink">Word for the Web:</strong> Home tab &rarr; <em>Add-ins</em> dropdown &rarr; <em>More Add-ins</em> &rarr; <em>My Add-ins</em> tab.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-ink">Word for iPad:</strong> Insert tab &rarr; <em>Add-ins</em>. Individual sideload is blocked by Apple, so your account admin needs to push the manifest via Microsoft 365 admin center. Once the AppSource listing is live, iPad installs become one tap.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-ink">Word for Android tablet:</strong> Word on Android does not support user-installed add-ins at all &mdash; not sideload, not AppSource. If you only have an Android tablet, finish this install on a Mac, Windows, or Word for the Web where your Microsoft account is signed in; the add-in follows your account.
      </li>
      <li class="text-ink-soft/80 pt-1">
        Stuck? See the <a href="/support" class="text-oxblood underline">support page</a> or email <a href="mailto:support@blackletter.studio" class="text-oxblood underline">support@blackletter.studio</a>.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  {/* ------- Step 2 ------- */}
  <section class="py-10 border-t border-black/10">
    <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-oxblood mb-3">Step 2</p>
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl mb-4">Click &ldquo;Upload My Add-in&rdquo;</h2>

    <p class="text-ink-soft max-w-2xl mb-6 leading-relaxed">
      In the &ldquo;My Add-ins&rdquo; tab of the dialog that opens, you&rsquo;ll see an <em>Upload My Add-in</em> link in the top-right corner. Click it &mdash; a file picker appears.
    </p>
  </section>

  {/* ------- Step 3 ------- */}
  <section class="py-10 border-t border-black/10">
    <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-oxblood mb-3">Step 3</p>
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl mb-4">Choose the manifest file you downloaded</h2>

    <p class="text-ink-soft max-w-2xl mb-6 leading-relaxed">
      Navigate to your Downloads folder, select <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-black/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">fair-copy-manifest.xml</code>, and click <em>Upload</em>. Word will validate it and install Fair Copy within a few seconds.
    </p>

    <p class="text-sm text-ink-soft max-w-2xl">
      You&rsquo;ll see a brief &ldquo;Fair Copy is loading&hellip;&rdquo; indicator, then the task pane opens on the right side of your document.
    </p>
  </section>

  {/* ------- Step 4 ------- */}
  <section class="py-10 border-t border-black/10">
    <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-oxblood mb-3">Step 4</p>
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl mb-4">You&rsquo;re done &mdash; open a document and try it</h2>

    <p class="text-ink-soft max-w-2xl mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      From now on, Fair Copy appears in Word&rsquo;s Home ribbon as a button labeled <em>Fair Copy</em>. Click it to open the task pane on any document. Your first five documents run in full, unrestricted mode &mdash; no card, no signup, no waiting.
    </p>

    <p class="text-sm text-ink-soft max-w-2xl">
      When you&rsquo;re ready for a lifetime license, click <em>Activate</em> in the task pane and enter your license code. Don&rsquo;t have one? Email <a href="mailto:hello@blackletter.studio?subject=Fair%20Copy%20license%20code" class="text-oxblood underline">hello@blackletter.studio</a> during early access and we&rsquo;ll send one.
    </p>

    <figure class="mt-8 max-w-2xl">
      <img
        src="/fair-copy/screenshots/hero-taskpane.png"
        alt="Fair Copy task pane open on the right side of a Word document, with the Clean document button centered in the pane."
        width="1600"
        height="900"
        loading="lazy"
        class="w-full rounded-md border border-black/10"
      />
      <figcaption class="text-xs text-ink-soft mt-2 italic">
        Fair Copy running on a cleaned document. The task pane stays on the right while you edit.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  {/* ------- Security reassurance ------- */}
  <section class="py-10 border-t border-black/10">
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl mb-4">Is sideload safe?</h2>
    <p class="text-ink-soft max-w-2xl mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Yes. Sideload is the same mechanism IT departments use to deploy custom Office tools inside a firm. The manifest is signed by Microsoft&rsquo;s validator when you upload it; the add-in itself is the same bundle we submit to AppSource. Nothing is pre-loaded with your data, and Fair Copy requests <em>ReadWriteDocument</em> permission only &mdash; it cannot see other files, your Outlook, or anything outside the Word document you&rsquo;re editing.
    </p>

    <p class="text-sm text-ink-soft max-w-2xl">
      Our full network-traffic inventory is on the <a href="/trust" class="text-oxblood underline">Trust page</a>, and the add-in source is <a href="https://github.com/blackletter-studio/fair-copy" class="text-oxblood underline">public on GitHub</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  {/* ------- Troubleshooting ------- */}
  <section class="py-10 border-t border-black/10">
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl mb-6">If something goes wrong</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6 max-w-2xl">
      <details class="border-l-2 border-oxblood/30 pl-6">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-display text-lg leading-tight">
          The Upload button is greyed out or missing.
        </summary>
        <p class="text-ink-soft mt-3 leading-relaxed text-sm">
          Your organization may have disabled user-side sideloading. Ask your IT admin to either (a) push the manifest to your account via Microsoft 365 admin center &rarr; <em>Integrated Apps</em> &rarr; <em>Upload custom apps</em>, or (b) temporarily enable personal add-ins under <em>Org settings &rarr; Services &rarr; User-owned apps</em>. The AppSource listing, once live, will bypass this restriction.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="border-l-2 border-oxblood/30 pl-6">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-display text-lg leading-tight">
          The task pane shows a blank screen or &ldquo;check your network connectivity&rdquo;.
        </summary>
        <p class="text-ink-soft mt-3 leading-relaxed text-sm">
          Usually a corporate firewall blocking <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-black/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">fair-copy-addin.pages.dev</code> or <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-black/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">fair-copy.blackletter.studio</code>. Both domains must be reachable &mdash; the first serves the add-in UI, the second handles license activation. If you&rsquo;re on VPN, try disabling it once to confirm the add-in works, then ask IT to allow those two domains.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="border-l-2 border-oxblood/30 pl-6">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-display text-lg leading-tight">
          I don&rsquo;t see the Fair Copy button in my ribbon.
        </summary>
        <p class="text-ink-soft mt-3 leading-relaxed text-sm">
          Fully quit Word (<em>Cmd+Q</em> on Mac, close all Word windows on Windows) and reopen. Add-in registration sometimes needs a restart to take effect. On Word for the Web, hard-refresh the browser tab.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="border-l-2 border-oxblood/30 pl-6">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-display text-lg leading-tight">
          Can I install once and use Fair Copy everywhere I sign in?
        </summary>
        <p class="text-ink-soft mt-3 leading-relaxed text-sm">
          Yes &mdash; once you sideload under a given Microsoft account, Fair Copy follows that account to Word on any device. Your license token is stored in <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-black/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">Office.context.roamingSettings</code>, which Microsoft syncs through your Microsoft 365 account (not ours).
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="border-l-2 border-oxblood/30 pl-6">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-display text-lg leading-tight">
          I&rsquo;m still stuck.
        </summary>
        <p class="text-ink-soft mt-3 leading-relaxed text-sm">
          Email <a href="mailto:support@blackletter.studio?subject=Fair%20Copy%20install%20help" class="text-oxblood underline">support@blackletter.studio</a> with a screenshot of what you&rsquo;re seeing and your Word version (Help &rarr; About). One human reads every message, and we aim to reply within two business days.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ------- Back link ------- */}
  <section class="py-12 border-t border-black/10">
    <p class="text-sm text-ink-soft">
      <a href="/fair-copy" class="text-oxblood underline">&larr; Back to Fair Copy</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
